* {{cite book
    |last = Cleland | first = Thomas M.
    |title = A practical description of the Munsell color system, with suggestions for its use
    |year = 1921
    |publisher = Munsell Color Company
    |location = Boston }}  One of the first books about the Munsell color system, explaining the intuition behind its three dimensions, and suggesting possible uses of the system in picking color combinations.  An edited version can be found at [http://www.applepainter.com/ http://www.applepainter.com/]{{Wayback|url=http://www.applepainter.com/ |date=20130514130813 }}.
* {{cite journal
    | last = Kuehni | first = Rolf G.
